You are given an array of integers. Your task is to check whether the array is a palindrome.

An array is a palindrome if it reads the same from left to right and right to left.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer n, representing the size of the array.

The second line contains n space-separated integers, representing the array elements.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

Print "Yes" if the array is a palindrome.

Print "No" otherwise.

Sample Input 0

5
1 2 3 2 1
Sample Output 0

Yes
Explanation 0

The array reads the same forward and backward: 1 2 3 2 1.

Sample Input 1

4
1 2 3 4
Sample Output 1

No
Explanation 1

The array reads 1 2 3 4 forward and 4 3 2 1 backward, which are not the same.


import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int size=sc.nextInt();
        int arr[]=new int[size];
        for(int i=0;i<size;i++) arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
        for(int i=0,j=size-1;i<j;i++,j--)
        {
            if(arr[i]==arr[j])
            {
                System.out.print("Yes");
                return;
            }
        }
        System.out.print("No");
    }
}
